Package org.soulwing.prospecto.api.association

Interface ToManyAssociationManager<T,​E>

  • All Superinterfaces:
    AssociationManager<T,​E>
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    ToManyIndexedAssociationManager<T,​E>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    AbstractArrayAssociationManager, AbstractCollectionAssociationManager, AbstractListAssociationManager, AbstractToManyAssociationManager, AbstractToManyIndexedAssociationManager
    public interface ToManyAssociationManager<T,​E>
extends AssociationManager<T,​E>
    An object that during view application manages the association between an object and a collection composed in the object.

    A manager is used, by the underlying framework, in a transactional fashion. Before invoking methods to update the associated collection, the framework will first invoke the begin(Object) method to inform the manager that a sequence of collection-operations will be performed. When all update operations have been performed, the framework will notify the manager that the update is complete by invoking the end(Object) method.

    Author:
    Carl Harris
